reviews.text:
Highly recommend this Thai restaurant!

The Pad Thai here is especially good ‚Äî they use glass noodles, which adds a nice texture.
The green curry, pineapple fried rice, and stir-fried eggplant were all delicious.
So glad I found this place!
We went there last 11/16/24 to celebrate my daughter's birthday. We LOVED everything we ordered except for the veggie rolls. üò¨ The server was so kind and helpful too. üëçüëç

We‚Äôve been enjoying this place since they opened, and it‚Äôs super cool that they do both Sushi and Thai under one roof. Locally owned and the chef has been consistent for well over a decade. Today we celebrated my daughters birthday dinner, and sushi was on our mind‚Ä¶.so we ordered hella rolls and grubbed down. Thai iced teas were tasty too. We‚Äôll be back over and over again. One love to Blue Mango!

This is my first time at this place (well, ordering food from here) and will definitely not be the last. The place is very welcoming, as soon as it is safe to eat again at the restaurants, I will not hesitate to come here. The place small really nice and looks very clean.¬†The staff is friendly and welcoming, and¬†they make sure they're handing you the right order.
Food verdict: Tasty, great portions, with the right temperature, texture,¬†colorful and textured and the have a wide menu.

I ordered the Dynamite roll (sweet potato, spicy avocado. Top: cucumber, jalapeno. Garnish with spicy sauce),¬† curly fries (with Panang sauce), Pai Thai (with pork), and a side of curry Dipping Sauce.

If you are craving or looking for a good Thai food option, this is your new place.

We were visiting from New Jersey and stumbled upon this eatery. The restaurant was clean, and the waiter was sweet and attentive.  The food was hot and tasty, and the portion was satisfying. I tried the Thai iced tea, and it was refreshing. I had the basil stirfry with chicken and a side of rice, while my wife had the red noodle; they were both great choices. I met the owner, and he was friendly, accommodating, and grateful. Great experience; now that's what I'm talking about.

editorial_summary.overview: Casual Thai eatery offering a variety of classic dishes, including dozens of vegetarian options.
